      • Problem

        public Problem(java.lang.String problemName,
               java.lang.String problemDescription,
               java.lang.String decisionVariablesSetName,
               DataType decisionVariablesDataType,
               java.lang.String decisionVariablesLowerBound,
               java.lang.String decisionVariablesUpperBound,
               java.lang.String decisionVariablesInvalidValues,
               java.util.ArrayList<DecisionVariable> decisionVariables,
               DataType optimizationCriteriaDataType,
               java.util.ArrayList<OptimizationCriteria> optimizationCriteria,
               java.lang.String fitnessFunction,
               java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> optimizationAlgorithms,
               java.lang.String idealTimeFrame,
               java.lang.String maxTimeFrame)
        Constructor for the Problem class. The list of known solutions is not initialized and, if necessary, it must be set using the setOptimizationAlgorithms(ArrayList optimizationAlgorithms) method
        Parameters:
        problemName - String containing the name of the problem. This name must follow the Java convention for class names
        problemDescription - [OPTIONAL] String containing the optimization problem's description in natural language
        decisionVariablesSetName - [OPTIONAL] String containing the name of the problem's set of decision variables
        decisionVariablesDataType - data type of the decision variables: DataType.INTEGER or DataType.DOUBLE or DataType.BINARY
        decisionVariablesLowerBound - lower bound for the values the variables can assume
        decisionVariablesUpperBound - upper bound for the values the variables can assume
        decisionVariablesInvalidValues - exception values to the lowerBound-upperBound interval [OPTIONAL]
        decisionVariables - List of all the problem's decision variables
        optimizationCriteriaDataType - data type of the optimizationCriteria: DataType.INTEGER or DataType.DOUBLE or DataType.BINARY
        fitnessFunction - String containing the path to the function's executable jar file
        optimizationAlgorithms - List of the optimization algorithms selected
        idealTimeFrame - Ideal time frame for the algorithm's runtime
        maxTimeFrame - [OPTIONAL] Maximum time frame accepted for the algorithm's runtime

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. Although this method can receive any object as an argument, it does not validate whether it is really an instantiated objected of the class Problem. Instead, this function assumes the object passed as an argument is a Problem Object.
